###Factors of $53$

$\begin{align}
\blueE{1} \times \blueE{53} &= \maroonD{53}
\end{align}$

All of the shaded numbers in the table are factors of $\maroonD{53}$.

There's a special name for numbers with exactly two factors! The number $\maroonD{53}$ is **prime**.

$\begin{align}
\blueE{1} \times \blueE{9} &= \maroonD{9}\\\\
\blueE{3} \times \blueE{3} &= \maroonD{9}
\end{align}$

So the factors of $\maroonD{9}$ are $\blueE{1}$, $\blueE{3}$, and $\blueE{9}$.

$\begin{align}
\blueE{1} \times \blueE{8} &= \maroonD{8}\\\\
\blueE{2} \times \blueE{4} &= \maroonD{8}
\end{align}$

So the factors of $\maroonD{8}$ are $\blueE{1}$, $\blueE{2}$, $\blueE{4}$, and $\blueE{8}$.

$\begin{align}
\blueE{1} \times \blueE{25} &= \maroonD{25}\\\\
\blueE{5} \times \blueE{5} &= \maroonD{25}
\end{align}$

So the factors of $\maroonD{25}$ are $\blueE{1}$, $\blueE{5}$, and $\blueE{25}$.
